<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,295,321]" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="2005" box="[279,562,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Mazarredia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lochengensis">
<emphasis box="[279,562,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">Mazarredia lochengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not a 
<taxonomicName box="[653,871,295,321]" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">
<emphasis box="[653,784,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">Mazarredia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
because lateral margins of vertex turned backward and slightly exerted above upper margin of eyes; in frontal view, vertex with V-shaped concavity. It belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar, 1817" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1817" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">Xistra</emphasis>
Bolívar, 1817
</taxonomicName>
. We have examined the 
<typeStatus box="[612,660,367,393]" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="2005" box="[818,1100,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Mazarredia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lochengensis">
<emphasis box="[818,1100,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">Mazarredia lochengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Deng &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="2014" box="[1153,1311,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[1153,1311,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">Xistra oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and found that structures and coloration of the body are the same in both taxa. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Deng &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="2014" box="[1045,1205,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[1045,1205,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">Xistra oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here considered a synonym of of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng" authorityYear="2005" box="[322,605,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Mazarredia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lochengensis">
<emphasis box="[322,605,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="195">Mazarredia lochengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
